summary: Can I order a #75 Kaminari? Plz?
question: Can I order a #75 Kaminari? Plz?
answer:
ORDER UP

___

“You fainted, straight into my arms. You know, if you wanted my attention, you didn’t have to go to such extremes.” Shinsou blinked, his gaze focusing on the face above him. Kaminari wore a signature smirk, his gold hair hanging over his face. His leather jacket was cold against Shinsou’s back.

Shinsou pushed Kaminari away, staggering to his feet. “I did not faint.”

Kaminari raised an eyebrow. “Sure you didn’t.”

“I did not faint! I went unconscious as a result of an unexpected enemy attack.” Shinsou protested. Flashes of the training mission went through his head, but Shinsou couldn’t pinpoint the exact moment he’d passed out.

“Most people call that fainting,” Kaminari said.

Shinsou bit his lip and dug the toe of his shoe into the dirt. “Whatever. It isn’t worth arguing over.” He turned around, but Shinsou could still feel Kaminari’s gaze on his back.

“You’re lucky I was there to catch you,” Kaminari said. “It’d be a shame to cause head damage to such a pretty face.”

“The only one with head damage around here is – wait, what?”

“What?” Kaminari furrowed his eyebrows. All at once, he seemed to realize the second part of his sentence. A red haze painted his cheeks and he broke Shinsou’s gaze, staring at the ground. “I’m just messing with you.” He mumbled.

“Right,” Shinsou cleared his throat. He took a deep breath, fighting to keep his voice steady. “Anyway. We still have to finish the training mission, don’t we?”

Kaminari shook out his hands. His face was still the color of a fire engine. “Yeah,” he agreed. “Let’s just…focus on that.”

Shinsou nodded, glad to leave behind the sudden tension in the air.

“Promise you won’t faint again,” Kaminari said as he adjusted the sleeves of his jacket.

“I didn’t faint!”

“Don’t worry. I’ll catch you again if you do.”

summary: Kirishima Eijirou : I have an idea for a new reality TV show. It's called... "The Bak-elor". 14 contestants compete to become...
body:
Kirishima Eijirou : I have an idea for a new reality TV show. It's called... "The Bak-elor". 14 contestants compete to become Bakugou's one and only nemesis. Instead of giving them a rose, he hands out a dirty sock.
Todoroki Shouto : Oh, I'm in. Roses fade. I could use a sock.
Midoriya Izuku : I can't decide which would be more humiliating: getting dumped first or Kacchan keeping me all the way up to the finale just to dump me at the last possible moment.
Iida Tenya : Invite Shigaraki as a contestant. It's the most well thought-out plan to capture him up to this point.
Uraraka Ochako : Does the winner get to fight Kacchan?
Bakugou Katsuki : Can we find a way for me to dump Monoma each week?
